org.perfcake.reporting.reporter.accumulator

Interface Accumulator<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSlidingWindowAccumulator, AbstractTimeSlidingWindowAccumulator, AvgAccumulator, HarmonicMeanAccumulator, LastValueAccumulator, MaxAccumulator, MaxLongValueAccumulator, MinAccumulator, SlidingWindowAvgAccumulator, SlidingWindowHarmonicMeanAccumulator, SlidingWindowMaxAccumulator, SlidingWindowMinAccumulator, SlidingWindowSumLongAccumulator, SumAccumulator, SumLongAccumulator, TimeSlidingWindowAvgAccumulator, TimeSlidingWindowHarmonicMeanAccumulator, TimeSlidingWindowMaxAccumulator, TimeSlidingWindowMinAccumulator, TimeSlidingWindowSumAccumulator, TimeSlidingWindowSumLongAccumulator, WeightedHarmonicMeanAccumulator, WeightedMeanAccumulator

    public interface Accumulator<T>
    Accumulator is a tool for reporters to accumulate multiple values from measurement units into a single mesurement. Accumulator must be thread safe as it might be called from multiple threads at the same time.
    Author:
    Martin Večeřa
